 ğŸ”„ 1. What is Lifecycle Policy in AWS S3?

 âœ… Definition

Lifecycle policy AWS S3 ka ek feature hai jisse hum automatically objects ko manage kar sakte hain, jaise:

 Storage class change karna (Standard â†’ IA â†’ Glacier)
 Old data delete karna
 Cost optimize karna

ğŸ‘‰ Matlab: manual kaam kam, automation zyada

---

 ğŸ¯ Why Lifecycle Policy is Used?

 Storage cost kam karne ke liye
 Old / unused data ko archive karne ke liye
 Long-term data ko delete karne ke liye
 Bucket clean aur optimized rakhne ke liye

---

 ğŸ§  Real-Life Example

ğŸ“± Mobile Photos

 New photos â†’ phone storage
 Old photos â†’ Google Photos backup
 Bahut purani photos â†’ archive / delete

ğŸ‘‰ Ye hi kaam S3 me lifecycle policy karti hai.

---

 ğŸªœ 2. Lifecycle Policy Steps in AWS (Practical Steps)

 ğŸ”¹ Step 1: Bucket Create hone ke baad

 S3 bucket open karo

---

 ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Go to Management Tab

 Bucket ke andar Management section par jao

---

 ğŸ”¹ Step 3: Lifecycle Rules

 Lifecycle rules option select karo
 Click Create lifecycle rule

---

 ğŸ”¹ Step 4: Rule Name

 Lifecycle rule ka naam do
  (example: `move-to-glacier-rule`)

---

 ğŸ”¹ Step 5: Lifecycle Rule Actions

Yahan 2 main actions hote hain:

 âœ… A. Transition Current Versions

 Objects ko ek storage class se doosri me move karta hai
 Example:

   30 days â†’ S3 Standard-IA
   90 days â†’ Glacier

---

 âœ… B. Expire Current Versions

 Objects ko permanently delete karta hai
 Example:

   365 days ke baad delete

---

 ğŸ”¹ Step 6: Days After Object Creation

 Specify karo kitne din baad transition / delete hoga

---

 ğŸ”¹ Step 7: Add Transition & Save

 Transition add karo
 Rule save karo

ğŸ‘‰ Lifecycle rule active ho jata hai.

